# ==========================================================
# V.A.D.I.S. Blueprint Notes
# ==========================================================

## Purpose

This document captures architectural decisions,
development principles and observations that emerge
during the implementation of V.A.D.I.S. software.

It is intentionally informal.

It explains **WHY** decisions were made,
not **HOW** they were implemented.

The goal is to preserve knowledge that will later
become part of the official V.A.D.I.S. Blueprint.


---

# Blueprint Note 000001

## Topic

Session Management

### Observation

Daily log files combine multiple application runs.

### Decision

Every application run receives its own unique Session ID.

### Result

Each program session produces exactly one log file.

### Future

The Session ID will later connect:

- Log files
- Screenshots
- Diagnostics
- Footer
- Crash Reports
- Export files

### Reason

Every artefact produced during one execution of the
program should always be traceable to exactly one session.


---

# Blueprint Note 000002

## Topic

Developer Footer

### Observation

Important diagnostic information should be visible
without opening log files.

### Decision

Every V.A.D.I.S. application provides a small
developer footer.

### Current Information

- Status
- Session ID
- Build Number

### Planned Extensions

- Version
- Git Revision
- Python Version
- Diagnostics Level
- Capture Mode

### Reason

A single screenshot should already provide sufficient
information to identify the executed software build.


---

# Blueprint Note 000003

## Topic

Commit Strategy

### Decision

**One Commit = One Idea**

### Reason

Every commit should describe one complete and
understandable architectural or functional step.

This creates a readable project history and
simplifies maintenance.


---

# Blueprint Note 000004

## Topic

Module Responsibility

### Decision

Each module owns exactly one responsibility.

### Examples

logger.py

- writes log entries

session.py

- creates the Session ID

version.py

- provides application information

gui.py

- creates the graphical user interface

filesystem.py

- file system operations

capture.py

- communication with Windows APIs

screenshot.py

- screenshot creation

### Reason

Small modules are easier to understand,
test and reuse.


---

# Blueprint Note 000005

## Topic

Evidence before Assumption

### Observation

During development, assumptions can easily be mistaken
for facts.

### Decision

Observations must always be verified before they
become implementation decisions.

### Reason

Software should be improved based on evidence,
not assumptions.

This principle also reflects the philosophy
behind GeoRecon.


---

# Blueprint Note 000006

## Topic

Architecture before Features

### Decision

Invest early in a stable architecture.

Features are added afterwards.

### Reason

A solid foundation reduces future complexity,
improves maintainability and allows new projects
to start from a proven structure.


---

# Blueprint Note 000007

## Topic

Internationalization

### Observation

Language support is an architectural concern,
not an optional feature.

### Decision

Future V.A.D.I.S. applications should avoid
hard-coded user interface text.

### Future

A dedicated language module will become part
of the standard project structure.

### Reason

Localization should be prepared from the
beginning rather than retrofitted later.


---

# Personal Observation

The V.A.D.I.S. Blueprint is not written first.

It emerges from practical development.

Every solved problem,
every successful refactoring,
every architectural decision
becomes part of the Blueprint.

The Blueprint is therefore a living document.
